docs.snippet: The United States has proposed that the first meeting of the intergovernmental committee for facilitating the emigration of political refugees from Austria and Germany be held in a Swiss city, it was disclosed today when France commented favorably on...
docs.lead_paragraph: The United States has proposed that the first meeting of the intergovernmental committee for facilitating the emigration of political refugees from Austria and Germany be held in a Swiss city, it was disclosed today when France commented favorably on the proposal in a note agreeing to cooperate. Italy, meanwhile, declined to do so.
docs.abstract: Swiss city chosen for com's 1st meeting; plan approved by France and 10 other countries; rejected by Italy
